September is National #SuicidePrevention Awareness Month.

This month, we encourage any veteran who may be going through a tough time to reach out ‚Äì you matter and it's okay not to be okay.

If you or someone you know is struggling, hope and help are available. #NotAlone pic.twitter.com/zdQDgyV5Dy
If you or a veteran you know is in crisis, free, confidential support is available 24/7 by calling the Veterans Crisis Line at 1-800-273-8255 and pressing 1, texting 838-255, or visiting veteranscrisisline.net. #NotAlone
S. 785 is a good, bipartisan bill to prevent veteran suicide and is supported by every single Senator from across the ideological spectrum ‚Äì from @SenKamalaHarris to @SenMikeLee to @SenSanders to @SenTomCotton + the VSO community. pic.twitter.com/w7zbDrRUlZ
We have been talking all Congress about how suicide prevention is our first priority. Now is the time to prove that it really is.

While this bipartisan bill won't end the tragedy of veteran suicide, it is certainly a step in the right direction.

